sh:","nickname from Middle English <i>mirie</i>, <i>merie</i>, <i>murie</i> ‘merry, pleasant’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’. Compare   Merry   1. This surname is established in Ireland (perhaps as an Anglicized form of an unidentified Gaelic name; compare   Marmion  ) as well as England.","there has probably been some confusion with <b>Marriman</b>, probably an occupational name meaning ‘servant of <i>Mary</i>’, from the female personal name <i>Mary</i> (see   Marie  ) + Middle English <i>man</i> in the sense ‘servant’, or perhaps a pet form of <i>Mary</i> using the hypocoristic suffix -<i>man</i>. The surname <i>Marriman</i> is now vanishingly rare in Britain and Ireland."]},{"name":"Marmon","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Gloucestershire):","variant of   Marmion  .","variant of <b>Marriman</b>, an occupational name meaning ‘servant of Mary’, from the female personal name <i>Mary</i> (see   Marie  ) + Middle English <i>man</i> in the sense ‘servant’."]}]},{"name":"Mazere","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Philippe.","French: variant of <b>Masure</b>, a topographic name from Old French <i>masure</i> ‘country house, house with land, estate’ (from Latin <i>mansura</i>), or a habitational name from any of several places called with this word, for example Le Masure in Audresselles (Pas-de-Calais), Le Mazure in Savoy, and Les Mazures in Ardennes.","Americanized form of Polish, Ukrainian, Rusyn or Jewish   Mazur  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mazur","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Polish Zbigniew, Andrzej, Beata, Jacek, Stanislaw, Wladyslaw, Wojciech, Zygmunt, Henryk, Lech, Piotr, Wieslaw.","Polish, Ukrainian, Rusyn, Czech, and Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic); Slovak (mainly <b>Mazúr</b>): habitational name for someone from the medieval province of Masovia in Poland (Polish <i>Mazowsze</i>), which includes modern Masuria.","Polish: nickname from <i>mazur</i> ‘rustic’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mazere Marmion was born about 1245, in Tamworth, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Philip Marmion, was 37 and her mother, Joan Kilpec, was 21. She had at least 1 daughter with Ralph Cromwell. She died before 26 January 1271, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1245–BEF 26 JAN 1271":"umbes 1245–enne 26. jaanuari 1271","1245–1271":"1245–1271","1262–1295":"1262–1295","1263–1316":"1263–1316","1214–1289":"1214–1289","1264–1339":"1264–1339","1210–1291":"1210–1291","1226–Female":"1226–Surnud","1264":"1264","1263":"1263","1295":"1295","1262":"1262","1271":"1271","1291":"1291","1316":"1316","1226":"1226","1214":"1214","Abt 1245":"umbes 1245","BEF 26 JAN 1271":"enne 26. jaanuari 1271","before 4 February 1244":"enne 4. veebruari 1244","1289":"1289","1245":"1245","Abt 1264":"umbes 1264","1210":"1210","1339":"1339","Tamworth Castle, Staffordshire, England":"Tamworth, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cromwell, Nottinghamshire, England":"Cromwell, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1245–BEF 26 JAN 1271":"noin 1245–ennen vuotta 26. tammikuuta 1271","1245–1271":"1245–1271","1262–1295":"1262–1295","1263–1316":"1263–1316","1214–1289":"1214–1289","1264–1339":"1264–1339","1210–1291":"1210–1291","1226–Female":"1226–Kuollut","1264":"1264","1263":"1263","1295":"1295","1262":"1262","1271":"1271","1291":"1291","1316":"1316","1226":"1226","1214":"1214","Abt 1245":"noin 1245","BEF 26 JAN 1271":"ennen vuotta 26. tammikuuta 1271","before 4 February 1244":"ennen vuotta 4. helmikuuta 1244","1289":"1289","1245":"1245","Abt 1264":"noin 1264","1210":"1210","1339":"1339","Tamworth Castle, Staffordshire, England":"Tamworth, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cromwell, Nottinghamshire, England":"Cromwell, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1245–BEF 26 JAN 1271":"environ 1245–avant 26 janvie